'''Alexander E. (Alex) Trotter''' was an [[English people|English]] [[Football (soccer)|footballer]].

==Playing career==
Trotter played for Jarrow, [[Ashington A.F.C.|Ashington]], [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] and [[South Shields F.C.|South Shields]]. Also guesting for [[Leeds City F.C.|Leeds City]], [[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]] and [[Raith Rovers F.C.|Raith Rovers]] during [[World War I|the war]]. Whilst with South shields, he seriously injured [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] goalkeeper [[Howard Matthews]], by charging him in the back in a 3-3 draw on 5 February 1927. Despite this, he signed for ''the Vale'' three months later. He was only to play 17 games for the club however and was given a [[free transfer (football)|free transfer]] to [[Manchester Central F.C.|Manchester Central]] in May 1928. He later moved on to Bedlington United.<ref>{{cite book|last=Kent|first=Jeff|title=Port Vale Personalities|publisher=Witan Books|page=293|date=1996|isbn=0952915200|url=http://www.amazon.ca/Port-Vale-Personalities-Jeff-Kent/dp/0952915200}}</ref>

